channel.title: My first comp was today...
channel.description:
Placed third. Was pretty excited.
Some pix (I'm 46):

item.description:

r;23724"]kaze, don’t you think that it’s too much?

today’s life is not that tough to grow the bio-armour,
also, don’t you think, it’d be more comfortable not to have these redundancies ?

just curious

The above doesn’t mean the following:

"Com[e:

r;24411"]kaze, don’t you think that it’s too much?
//as i was rly interested in what is it like - to have so much muscules?

In fact it pretty much doesn’t mean anything.

Whereas:

Kaze:

What the fuck are you on about?

very much does mean “I didn’t understand you, what are you trying to say?”

wheybags:

Am I the only one that actually understood all of com[e]r’s posts immediately, and thinks everyone is just flaming him for having a different point of view?

I can count on one hand the number of posts he’s ever made that I’ve understood. I’ve never once comprehended his point of view enough to know whether I agree with it or not, so I’ve never before flamed him or even responded to him.

[COLOR=‘Red’]Anyway, let’s all move on now.
